!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

reluctant /rɪˈlʌktənt/

1. ADJ If you are reluctant to do something, you are unwilling to do it and hesitate before doing it, or do it slowly and without enthusiasm. 不愿意的; 勉强的 

例： Mr. Spero was reluctant to ask for help. 斯珀洛先生不愿意请求帮助。 

2. reluctantly ADV 不愿意地; 勉强地 [ADV with v] 

例： We have reluctantly agreed to let him go. 我们已勉强同意让他走了。

</div>

